ZooKeeper / Zab  —  benchmark groups ZooKeeper, ZooKeeper_LowLevel
    TLA+ specifications of ZooKeeper's Zab atomic-broadcast protocol and of the
    apache/zookeeper v3.7.0 implementation, from the Remix paper
    (arXiv:2409.14301, https://arxiv.org/abs/2409.14301). The Zab protocol is
    described in Junqueira, Reed, and Serafini, "Zab: High-performance broadcast
    for primary-backup systems" (DSN 2011); the modeled system is
    https://github.com/apache/zookeeper (Apache-2.0).

Ivy liveness examples  —  benchmark groups prefixed `ivy_examples_`
    TLA+ translations of liveness examples from the Ivy verification system
    (https://github.com/kenmcmil/ivy, examples/liveness/, MIT).
    Copyright (c) Microsoft Corporation.

two_thread_mutex  —  MIT  —  benchmark group two_thread_mutex
    TLA+ model of src/tla_demo.rs from the Anvil repository
    (https://github.com/anvil-verifier/anvil), a standalone two-thread
    mutual-exclusion example included there to illustrate TLA+ usage. It is not
    part of Anvil's verified Kubernetes-controller proofs.
    Copyright 2022 VMware, Inc.

etcd / Specula  —  benchmark group etcd_raft
    From the Specula etcd-raft reference model (https://github.com/specula-org),
    derived from the raft TLA+ specification in etcd
    (https://github.com/etcd-io/etcd). Copyright 2024 The etcd Authors;
    licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0
    (http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0).

AbstractRaft  —  unvalidated proof exercise
    Contributed by Stephan Merz and retained under
    unvalidated-proof-exercises/proof-from-scratch/AbstractRaft as a standalone,
    Raft-inspired TLA+ proof exercise. Its refinement relationship to Raft has
    not been established. Raft is described by Diego Ongaro and John Ousterhout,
    "In Search of an Understandable Consensus Algorithm", USENIX ATC 2014.


